  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-ON-02 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed. All 13 credibility factors are assessed; achieved levels meet or exceed required levels, yielding an Accepted decision. The ContextOfUse description enumerates operating ranges (temperature 36–38 °C, inlet pressure 5–20 mmHg, flow rate 3–6 L/min, rotational speed 2400–3200 RPM, turbulent-laminar transitional regime Re 1500–4500) in sufficient detail that a reviewer may assume these constitute a formal operating envelope — but no hasOperatingEnvelope or hasApplicabilityConstraint link is emitted, leaving the model's range of valid use ontologically unspecified.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/vad-hemolysis-cfd-accepted",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/cfd-hemolysis-centrifugal-pump",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-piv-experimental",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-hemolysis-bench",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/montecarlo-uncertainty-samples"
  ],
  "hasContextOfUse": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cou/cou2-vad",
    "type": "ContextOfUse",
    "name": "COU2: Ventricular assist device use (Class III)",
    "description": "A CFD model is used to predict absolute hemolysis levels across operating conditions for a centrifugal blood pump used as a ventricular assist device (VAD). The device operates within the following ranges, as enumerated in the simulation protocol: blood temperature 36–38 °C, inlet static pressure 5–20 mmHg, outlet pressure 80–120 mmHg, volumetric flow rate 3–6 L/min, impeller rotational speed 2400–3200 RPM, and a transitional-to-turbulent flow regime (Reynolds number 1500–4500 based on inlet diameter). Non-Newtonian blood viscosity is modelled using the Carreau–Yasuda constitutive relation calibrated at 37 °C. These parameter ranges are drawn from the simulation test matrix and reflect the conditions under which predictions are reported. Model influence is HIGH (model is primary basis for hemolysis acceptance); decision consequence is HIGH (incorrect prediction could result in chronic patient hemolysis requiring clinical intervention). Model Risk Level 5 — the highest in the Morrison assessment.",
    "intendedUse": "Use CFD to predict absolute hemolysis index values for a Class III VAD device across 5 flow-speed combinations. Results must demonstrate hemolysis below absolute clinical threshold (not relative to predicate). Requires Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification on hemolysis predictions.",
    "deviceClass": "Class III",
    "modelInfluence": "High",
    "decisionConsequence": "High"
  },
